
[1]aberrance

   ABER'RANCE, [L. aberrans, aberro, to wander from; of ab and ABER'RANCY,
   erro, to wander.]

   A wandering or deviating from the right way, but rarely used in a
   literal sense. In a figurative sense, a deviation from truth, error,
   mistake; and in morals, a fault, a deviation from rectitude.
